<analysis>**original_problem_statement:**
The user wants to perfect the invoice scanning feature for their mobile application, CalcAuto AiPro. The primary goal is to achieve flawless, correctly ordered data extraction from Stellantis (FCA) invoices. Several features have been requested:
*   A hybrid workflow to export OCR scan data to an Excel file for manual correction and later import, aiming for 100% data accuracy.
*   Ability to send financing submissions via SMS and a preview modal.
*   An option to Print submission details with a format as rich as the email.

**PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS:**
*   **Invoice Parser Perfection (P0):** The parser logic must be fixed to preserve the exact order of vehicle options, correctly identify vehicle trims, and filter out all irrelevant text from the invoice header and body. This is a recurring, high-priority issue.
*   **Complete Excel Workflow (P1):** The user has approved a hybrid OCR/Excel strategy. The export and import functionalities need to be fully implemented and working reliably on the frontend.
*   **UI/UX Bug Fixes (P1):** UI issues, such as buttons not appearing correctly, need to be resolved.
*   **Code Refactoring (P2):** The monolithic files  and  are slated for refactoring to improve maintainability.

**User's preferred language**: French. The next agent MUST respond in French.

**what currently exists?**
A full-stack application with a React Native (Expo) frontend and a FastAPI backend. The core feature is an invoice scanner for FCA vehicles.

The parser has been significantly overhauled and now uses a two-stage hybrid approach:
1.  **Google Cloud Vision** performs raw text extraction from the invoice image.
2.  **OpenAI's GPT-4o** is then used to structure the extracted raw text into a clean, ordered JSON, solving the long-standing option-ordering issue. The old regex-based parser is now a fallback.

The frontend features an Excel import/export workflow, an SMS sharing feature, and an improved print function that generates a rich HTML layout. A major refactoring of the monolithic  file has begun, with types and calculation logic extracted into separate hooks and type files.

However, the development environment is currently broken due to hardcoded deployment URLs in the frontend code, preventing automatic updates.

**Last working item**:
*   **Last item agent was working:** The user reported that the application was not deploying or hot-reloading automatically. The agent identified that this was caused by hardcoded URLs pointing to a previous  deployment in several frontend files. The agent was in the process of finding and replacing all instances with the correct  environment variable.
*   **Status:** IN PROGRESS
*   **Agent Testing Done:** N
*   **Which testing method agent to use?** Manual  command to find all remaining hardcoded URLs. After fixing them, use the screenshot tool to confirm the frontend loads and can communicate with the backend.
*   **User Testing Done:** N

**All Pending/In progress Issue list**:
*   **Issue 1: Deployment/Hot-Reload Failure (P0)**
    *   **Description:** The application does not automatically deploy or update on code changes because of hardcoded URLs pointing to a stale  deployment. This is a critical environment blocker.
    *   **Attempted fixes:** The agent identified three files (, , ) with the hardcoded URL and was searching for more.

  currency: 'CAD',\n      minimumFractionDigits: 0\n    }).format(amount);\n    const callContact = phone => Linking.default.openURL(`tel:${phone}`);\n    const emailContact = email => Linking.default.openURL(`mailto:${email}`);\n\n    // ============================================\n    // PARSE vCard FILE\n    // ============================================\n    const parseVCard = content => {\n      const contacts = [];\n      const vcards = content.split('END:VCARD');\n      for (const vcard of vcards) {\n        if (!vcard.includes('BEGIN:VCARD')) continue;\n        let name = '';\n        let phone = '';\n        let email = '';\n        const lines = vcard.split(/\\r?\\n/);\n        for (const line of lines) {\n          // Parse name (FN = Full Name)\n          if (line.startsWith('FN:') || line.startsWith('FN;')) {\n            name = line.split(':').slice(1).join(':').trim();\n          }\n          // Parse phone\n          if (line.startsWith('TEL') || line.includes('TEL;') || line.includes('TEL:')) {\n            const phoneMatch = line.match(/:([\\d\\s\\-\\+\\(\\)]+)/);\n            if (phoneMatch) {\n              phone = phoneMatch[1].trim();\n            }\n          }\n          // Parse email\n          if (line.startsWith('EMAIL') || line.includes('EMAIL;') || line.includes('EMAIL:')) {\n            const emailMatch = line.match(/:(.+@.+)/);\n            if (emailMatch) {\n              email = emailMatch[1].trim();\n            }\n          }\n        }\n        if (name) {\n          contacts.push({\n            id: `import_${Date.now()}_${contacts.length}`,\n            name,\n            phone,\n            email\n          });\n        }\n      }\n      return contacts;\n    };\n\n    // ============================================\n    // PARSE CSV FILE\n    // ============================================\n    const parseCSV = content => {\n      const contacts = [];\n      const lines = content.split(/\\r?\\n/);\n      if (lines.length < 2) return contacts;\n\n      // Parse header to find column indices\n      const header = lines[0].toLowerCase();\n      const headers = header.split(',').map(h => h.trim().replace(/\"/g, ''));\n      const nameIdx = headers.findIndex(h => h.includes('name') || h.includes('nom'));\n      const firstNameIdx = headers.findIndex(h => h.includes('first') || h.includes('prnom') || h.includes('prenom'));\n      const lastNameIdx = headers.findIndex(h => h.includes('last') || h.includes('family') || h.includes('nom de famille'));\n      const phoneIdx = headers.findIndex(h => h.includes('phone') || h.includes('tlphone') || h.includes('telephone') || h.includes('mobile'));\n      const emailIdx = headers.findIndex(h => h.includes('email') || h.includes('mail') || h.includes('courriel'));\n      for (let i = 1; i < lines.length; i++) {\n        const line = lines[i];\n        if (!line.trim()) continue;\n\n        // Simple CSV parsing (doesn't handle all edge cases but works for most exports)\n        const values = line.split(',').map(v => v.trim().replace(/^\"|\"$/g, ''));\n        let name = '';\n        if (nameIdx >= 0 && values[nameIdx]) {\n          name = values[nameIdx];\n        } else if (firstNameIdx >= 0 || lastNameIdx >= 0) {\n          const firstName = firstNameIdx >= 0 ? values[firstNameIdx] || '' : '';\n          const lastName = lastNameIdx >= 0 ? values[lastNameIdx] || '' : '';\n          name = `${firstName} ${lastName}`.trim();\n        }\n        const phone = phoneIdx >= 0 ? values[phoneIdx] || '' : '';\n        const email = emailIdx >= 0 ? values[emailIdx] || '' : '';\n        if (name) {\n          contacts.push({\n            id: `import_${Date.now()}_${contacts.length}`,\n            name,\n            phone,\n            email\n          });\n        }\n      }\n      return contacts;\n    };\n\n    // ============================================\n    // IMPORT FILE (vCard or CSV)\n    // ============================================\n    const importFile = async type => {\n      setImportingFile(true);\n      try {\n        const result = await DocumentPicker.getDocumentAsync({\n          type: type === 'vcard' ? ['text/vcard', 'text/x-vcard', '*/*'] : ['text/csv', 'text/comma-separated-values', '*/*'],\n          copyToCacheDirectory: true\n        });\n        if (result.canceled || !result.assets || result.assets.length === 0) {\n          setImportingFile(false);\n          return;\n        }\n        const file = result.assets[0];\n        console.log('Selected file:', file.name, file.uri);\n\n        // Read file content\n        let content = '';\n        if (Platform.default.OS === 'web') {\n          // For web, fetch the file\n          const response = await fetch(file.uri);\n          content = await response.text();\n        } else {\n          // For native, use FileSystem\n          const FileSystem = require(_dependencyMap[23], \"expo-file-system\");\n          content = await FileSystem.readAsStringAsync(file.uri);\n        }\n\n        // Parse based on file type\n        let contacts = [];\n        if (type === 'vcard' || file.name?.toLowerCase().endsWith('.vcf')) {\n          contacts = parseVCard(content);\n        } else {\n          contacts = parseCSV(content);\n        }\n        console.log(`Parsed ${contacts.length} contacts`);\n        if (contacts.length === 0) {\n          Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(crm.noContactsFound) : Alert.default.alert('Info', crm.noContactsFound);\n          setImportingFile(false);\n          return;\n        }\n\n        // SAVE CONTACTS TO DATABASE\n        try {\n          const headers = await getAuthHeaders();\n          const contactsToSave = contacts.map(c => ({\n            name: c.name,\n            phone: c.phone,\n            email: c.email,\n            source: 'import'\n          }));\n          const saveResponse = await axios.default.post(`${API_URL}/api/contacts/bulk`, {\n            contacts: contactsToSave\n          }, {\n            headers\n          });\n          console.log('Save response:', saveResponse.data);\n          const {\n            imported,\n            skipped\n          } = saveResponse.data;\n          Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(` ${imported} ${crm.importSuccess}${skipped > 0 ? ` (${skipped} doublons ignors)` : ''}`) : Alert.default.alert('', `${imported} ${crm.importSuccess}${skipped > 0 ? `\\n(${skipped} doublons ignors)` : ''}`);\n        } catch (saveErr) {\n          console.error('Error saving contacts:', saveErr);\n          //    };\n\n    // ============================================\n    // OTHER ACTIONS\n    // ============================================\n\n    const markReminderDone = async submissionId => {\n offerIgnored: 'Offer ignored',\n      offersFound: 'offer(s) found!',\n      noNewOffers: 'No new offers found'\n    }\n  };\n  function ClientsScreen() {\n    _s();\n    const router = (0, _expoRouter.useRouter)();\n    const {\n      getToken\n    } = (0, _contextsAuthContext.useAuth)();\n    const [lang, setLang] = (0, _react.useState)('fr');\n    const crm = crmTranslations[lang];\n    const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = (0, _react.useState)('clients');\n    const [clients, setClients] = (0, _react.useState)([]);\n    const [submissions, setSubmissions] = (0, _react.useState)([]);\n    const [filteredClients, setFilteredClients] = (0, _react.useState)([]);\n    const [searchQuery, setSearchQuery] = (0, _react.useState)('');\n    const [loading, setLoading] = (0, _react.useState)(true);\n    const [refreshing, setRefreshing] = (0, _react.useState)(false);\n\n    // Reminders\n    const [reminders, setReminders] = (0, _react.useState)([]);\n    const [remindersCount, setRemindersCount] = (0, _react.useState)(0);\n\n    // Better offers\n    const [betterOffers, setBetterOffers] = (0, _react.useState)([]);\n    const [checkingOffers, setCheckingOffers] = (0, _react.useState)(false);\n    const [approvingOffer, setApprovingOffer] = (0, _react.useState)(null);\n\n    // Import contacts modal\n    const [showImportModal, setShowImportModal] = (0, _react.useState)(false);\n    const [importedContacts, setImportedContacts] = (0, _react.useState)([]);\n    const [showImportedContactsModal, setShowImportedContactsModal] = (0, _react.useState)(false);\n    const [importingFile, setImportingFile] = (0, _react.useState)(false);\n\n    // Client details modal\n    const [selectedClient, setSelectedClient] = (0, _react.useState)(null);\n    const [showClientModal, setShowClientModal] = (0, _react.useState)(false);\n\n    // Follow-up modal\n    const [showFollowUpModal, setShowFollowUpModal] = (0, _react.useState)(false);\n    const [selectedSubmission, setSelectedSubmission] = (0, _react.useState)(null);\n    const [followUpDate, setFollowUpDate] = (0, _react.useState)('');\n    const [followUpNotes, setFollowUpNotes] = (0, _react.useState)('');\n    const [savingFollowUp, setSavingFollowUp] = (0, _react.useState)(false);\n\n    // Helper function to get auth headers\n    const getAuthHeaders = async () => {\n      const token = await getToken();\n      return token ? {\n        Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`\n      } : {};\n    };\n    (0, _react.useEffect)(() => {\n      (0, _utilsI18n.loadLanguage)().then(setLang);\n    }, []);\n    const handleLanguageChange = (0, _react.useCallback)(newLang => {\n      setLang(newLang);\n      (0, _utilsI18n.saveLanguage)(newLang);\n    }, []);\n    const loadData = async () => {\n      try {\n        const headers = await getAuthHeaders();\n\n        // Load submissions\n        const response = await axios.default.get(`${API_URL}/api/submissions`, {\n          headers\n        });\n        const allSubmissions = response.data;\n        setSubmissions(allSubmissions);\n\n        // Load better offers\n        try {\n          const offersResponse = await axios.default.get(`${API_URL}/api/better-offers`, {\n            headers\n          });\n          setBetterOffers(offersResponse.data);\n        } catch (err) {\n          console.log('Could not load better offers:', err);\n        }\n\n        // Load saved contacts from database\n        let savedContacts = [];\n        try {\n          const contactsResponse = await axios.default.get(`${API_URL}/api/contacts`, {\n            headers\n          });\n          savedContacts = contactsResponse.data;\n          console.log(`Loaded ${savedContacts.length} saved contacts`);\n        } catch (contactErr) {\n          console.log('Could not load saved contacts:', contactErr);\n        }\n\n        // Build clients from submissions\n        const clientsMap = new Map();\n        for (const sub of allSubmissions) {\n          const key = sub.client_phone || sub.client_email || sub.client_name;\n          if (!clientsMap.has(key)) clientsMap.set(key, []);\n          clientsMap.get(key).push(sub);\n        }\n        const clientsArray = [];\n\n        // Add clients from submissions\n        clientsMap.forEach(subs => {\n          const sortedSubs = subs.sort((a, b) => new Date(b.submission_date).getTime() - new Date(a.submission_date).getTime());\n          const latestSub = sortedSubs[0];\n          const pendingReminders = subs.filter(s => s.reminder_date && !s.reminder_done);\n          const nextReminder = pendingReminders.length > 0 ? pendingReminders.sort((a, b) => new Date(a.reminder_date).getTime() - new Date(b.reminder_date).getTime())[0].reminder_date : null;\n          clientsArray.push({\n            name: latestSub.client_name,\n            email: latestSub.client_email,\n            phone: latestSub.client_phone,\n            submissions: sortedSubs,\n            last_submission_date: latestSub.submission_date,\n            next_reminder: nextReminder,\n            has_pending_reminder: pendingReminders.length > 0\n          });\n        });\n\n        // Add imported contacts that are not already in clients list\n        const existingKeys = new Set(clientsArray.map(c => (c.phone || c.email || c.name).toLowerCase()));\n        for (const contact of savedContacts) {\n          const key = (contact.phone || contact.email || contact.name).toLowerCase();\n          if (!existingKeys.has(key)) {\n            clientsArray.push({\n              name: contact.name,\n              email: contact.email,\n              phone: contact.phone,\n              submissions: [],\n              last_submission_date: contact.created_at || new Date().toISOString(),\n              next_reminder: null,\n              has_pending_reminder: false\n            });\n            existingKeys.add(key);\n          }\n        }\n        clientsArray.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));\n        setClients(clientsArray);\n        setFilteredClients(clientsArray);\n\n        // Get pending reminders\n        const pendingReminders = allSubmissions.filter(s => s.reminder_date && !s.reminder_done);\n        setReminders(pendingReminders.sort((a, b) => new Date(a.reminder_date).getTime() - new Date(b.reminder_date).getTime()));\n        setRemindersCount(pendingReminders.length);\n      } catch (err) {\n        console.error('Error loading data:', err);\n      } finally {\n        setLoading(false);\n        setRefreshing(false);\n      }\n    };\n    (0, _react.useEffect)(() => {\n      loadData();\n    }, []);\n    (0, _react.useEffect)(() => {\n      if (!searchQuery.trim()) {\n        setFilteredClients(clients);\n      } else {\n        const query = searchQuery.toLowerCase();\n        setFilteredClients(clients.filter(c => c.name.toLowerCase().includes(query) || c.phone?.toLowerCase().includes(query) || c.email?.toLowerCase().includes(query)));\n      }\n    }, [searchQuery, clients]);\n    const onRefresh = () => {\n      setRefreshing(true);\n      loadData();\n    };\n    const getDaysUntil = dateStr => {\n      const today = new Date();\n      today.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);\n      const date = new Date(dateStr);\n      date.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);\n      return Math.ceil((date.getTime() - today.getTime()) / 86400000);\n    };\n    const getDueDateText = days => {\n      if (days < 0) return crm.overdue;\n      if (days === 0) return crm.dueToday;\n      if (days === 1) return crm.dueTomorrow;\n      return crm.inDays.replace('{n}', String(days));\n    };\n    const formatDate = dateStr => new Date(dateStr).toLocaleDateString(lang === 'fr' ? 'fr-CA' : 'en-CA', {\n      day: 'numeric',\n      month: 'short',\n      year: 'numeric'\n    });\n    const formatCurrency = amount => new Intl.NumberFormat('fr-CA', {\n      style: 'currency',\n      currency: 'CAD',\n      minimumFractionDigits: 0\n    }).format(amount);\n    const callContact = phone => Linking.default.openURL(`tel:${phone}`);\n    const emailContact = email => Linking.default.openURL(`mailto:${email}`);\n\n    // ============================================\n    // PARSE vCard FILE\n    // ============================================\n    const parseVCard = content => {\n      const contacts = [];\n      const vcards = content.split('END:VCARD');\n      for (const vcard of vcards) {\n        if (!vcard.includes('BEGIN:VCARD')) continue;\n        let name = '';\n        let phone = '';\n        let email = '';\n        const lines = vcard.split(/\\r?\\n/);\n        for (const line of lines) {\n          // Parse name (FN = Full Name)\n          if (line.startsWith('FN:') || line.startsWith('FN;')) {\n            name = line.split(':').slice(1).join(':').trim();\n          }\n          // Parse phone\n          if (line.startsWith('TEL') || line.includes('TEL;') || line.includes('TEL:')) {\n            const phoneMatch = line.match(/:([\\d\\s\\-\\+\\(\\)]+)/);\n            if (phoneMatch) {\n              phone = phoneMatch[1].trim();\n            }\n          }\n          // Parse email\n          if (line.startsWith('EMAIL') || line.includes('EMAIL;') || line.includes('EMAIL:')) {\n            const emailMatch = line.match(/:(.+@.+)/);\n            if (emailMatch) {\n              email = emailMatch[1].trim();\n            }\n          }\n        }\n        if (name) {\n          contacts.push({\n            id: `import_${Date.now()}_${contacts.length}`,\n            name,\n            phone,\n            email\n          });\n        }\n      }\n      return contacts;\n    };\n\n    // ============================================\n    // PARSE CSV FILE\n    // ============================================\n    const parseCSV = content => {\n      const contacts = [];\n      const lines = content.split(/\\r?\\n/);\n      if (lines.length < 2) return contacts;\n\n      // Parse header to find column indices\n      const header = lines[0].toLowerCase();\n      const headers = header.split(',').map(h => h.trim().replace(/\"/g, ''));\n      const nameIdx = headers.findIndex(h => h.includes('name') || h.includes('nom'));\n      const firstNameIdx = headers.findIndex(h => h.includes('first') || h.includes('prnom') || h.includes('prenom'));\n      const lastNameIdx = headers.findIndex(h => h.includes('last') || h.includes('family') || h.includes('nom de famille'));\n      const phoneIdx = headers.findIndex(h => h.includes('phone') || h.includes('tlphone') || h.includes('telephone') || h.includes('mobile'));\n      const emailIdx = headers.findIndex(h => h.includes('email') || h.includes('mail') || h.includes('courriel'));\n      for (let i = 1; i < lines.length; i++) {\n        const line = lines[i];\n        if (!line.trim()) continue;\n\n        // Simple CSV parsing (doesn't handle all edge cases but works for most exports)\n        const values = line.split(',').map(v => v.trim().replace(/^\"|\"$/g, ''));\n        let name = '';\n        if (nameIdx >= 0 && values[nameIdx]) {\n          name = values[nameIdx];\n        } else if (firstNameIdx >= 0 || lastNameIdx >= 0) {\n          const firstName = firstNameIdx >= 0 ? values[firstNameIdx] || '' : '';\n          const lastName = lastNameIdx >= 0 ? values[lastNameIdx] || '' : '';\n          name = `${firstName} ${lastName}`.trim();\n        }\n        const phone = phoneIdx >= 0 ? values[phoneIdx] || '' : '';\n        const email = emailIdx >= 0 ? values[emailIdx] || '' : '';\n        if (name) {\n          contacts.push({\n            id: `import_${Date.now()}_${contacts.length}`,\n            name,\n            phone,\n            email\n          });\n        }\n      }\n      return contacts;\n    };\n\n    // ============================================\n    // IMPORT FILE (vCard or CSV)\n    // ============================================\n    const importFile = async type => {\n      setImportingFile(true);\n      try {\n        const result = await DocumentPicker.getDocumentAsync({\n          type: type === 'vcard' ? ['text/vcard', 'text/x-vcard', '*/*'] : ['text/csv', 'text/comma-separated-values', '*/*'],\n          copyToCacheDirectory: true\n        });\n        if (result.canceled || !result.assets || result.assets.length === 0) {\n          setImportingFile(false);\n          return;\n        }\n        const file = result.assets[0];\n        console.log('Selected file:', file.name, file.uri);\n\n        // Read file content\n        let content = '';\n        if (Platform.default.OS === 'web') {\n          // For web, fetch the file\n          const response = await fetch(file.uri);\n          content = await response.text();\n        } else {\n          // For native, use FileSystem\n          const FileSystem = require(_dependencyMap[23], \"expo-file-system\");\n          content = await FileSystem.readAsStringAsync(file.uri);\n        }\n\n        // Parse based on file type\n        let contacts = [];\n        if (type === 'vcard' || file.name?.toLowerCase().endsWith('.vcf')) {\n          contacts = parseVCard(content);\n        } else {\n          contacts = parseCSV(content);\n        }\n        console.log(`Parsed ${contacts.length} contacts`);\n        if (contacts.length === 0) {\n          Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(crm.noContactsFound) : Alert.default.alert('Info', crm.noContactsFound);\n          setImportingFile(false);\n          return;\n        }\n\n        // SAVE CONTACTS TO DATABASE\n        try {\n          const headers = await getAuthHeaders();\n          const contactsToSave = contacts.map(c => ({\n            name: c.name,\n            phone: c.phone,\n            email: c.email,\n            source: 'import'\n          }));\n          const saveResponse = await axios.default.post(`${API_URL}/api/contacts/bulk`, {\n            contacts: contactsToSave\n          }, {\n            headers\n          });\n          console.log('Save response:', saveResponse.data);\n          const {\n            imported,\n            skipped\n          } = saveResponse.data;\n          Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(` ${imported} ${crm.importSuccess}${skipped > 0 ? ` (${skipped} doublons ignors)` : ''}`) : Alert.default.alert('', `${imported} ${crm.importSuccess}${skipped > 0 ? `\\n(${skipped} doublons ignors)` : ''}`);\n        } catch (saveErr) {\n          console.error('Error saving contacts:', saveErr);\n          // Still show the contacts even if save failed\n        }\n        setImportedContacts(contacts);\n        setShowImportModal(false);\n        setShowImportedContactsModal(true);\n      } catch (err) {\n        console.error('Error importing file:', err);\n        Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(crm.importError) : Alert.default.alert('Erreur', crm.importError);\n      } finally {\n        setImportingFile(false);\n      }\n    };\n\n    // Select imported contact and go to calculator\n    const selectImportedContact = contact => {\n      setShowImportedContactsModal(false);\n      router.push({\n        pathname: '/(tabs)',\n        params: {\n          clientName: contact.name,\n          clientEmail: contact.email,\n          clientPhone: contact.phone\n        }\n      });\n    };\n\n    // ============================================\n    // OTHER ACTIONS\n    // ============================================\n\n    const markReminderDone = async submissionId => {\n      try {\n        const headers = await getAuthHeaders();\n        await axios.default.put(`${API_URL}/api/submissions/${submissionId}/done`, {}, {\n          headers\n        });\n        await loadData();\n        Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(' Rappel complt!') : Alert.default.alert('', 'Rappel complt!');\n      } catch (err) {\n        console.error('Error marking done:', err);\n      }\n    };\n    const deleteReminder = async submissionId => {\n      const confirmDelete = () => {\n        return new Promise(resolve => {\n          if (Platform.default.OS === 'web') {\n            resolve(window.confirm('Supprimer ce rappel?'));\n          } else {\n            Alert.default.alert('Confirmer', 'Supprimer ce rappel?', [{\n              text: 'Annuler',\n              style: 'cancel',\n              onPress: () => resolve(false)\n            }, {\n              text: 'Supprimer',\n              style: 'destructive',\n              onPress: () => resolve(true)\n            }]);\n          }\n        });\n      };\n      const confirmed = await confirmDelete();\n      if (!confirmed) return;\n      try {\n        const headers = await getAuthHeaders();\n        await axios.default.delete(`${API_URL}/api/submissions/${submissionId}/reminder`, {\n          headers\n        });\n        await loadData();\n        Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(' Rappel supprim!') : Alert.default.alert('', 'Rappel supprim!');\n      } catch (err) {\n        console.error('Error deleting reminder:', err);\n      }\n    };\n    const deleteSubmission = async submissionId => {\n      const confirmDelete = () => {\n        return new Promise(resolve => {\n          if (Platform.default.OS === 'web') {\n            resolve(window.confirm('Supprimer cette soumission? Cette action est irrversible.'));\n          } else {\n            Alert.default.alert('Confirmer', 'Supprimer cette soumission? Cette action est irrversible.', [{\n              text: 'Annuler',\n              style: 'cancel',\n              onPress: () => resolve(false)\n            }, {\n              text: 'Supprimer',\n              style: 'destructive',\n              onPress: () => resolve(true)\n            }]);\n          }\n        });\n      };\n      const confirmed = await confirmDelete();\n      if (!confirmed) return;\n      try {\n        const headers = await getAuthHeaders();\n        await axios.default.delete(`${API_URL}/api/submissions/${submissionId}`, {\n          headers\n        });\n        await loadData();\n        Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(' Soumission supprime!') : Alert.default.alert('', 'Soumission supprime!');\n      } catch (err) {\n        console.error('Error deleting submission:', err);\n      }\n    };\n    const deleteContactHistory = async contactId => {\n      const confirmDelete = () => {\n        return new Promise(resolve => {\n          if (Platform.default.OS === 'web') {\n            resolve(window.confirm('Supprimer tout l\\'historique de ce contact? Cette action est irrversible.'));\n          } else {\n            Alert.default.alert('Confirmer', 'Supprimer tout l\\'historique de ce contact? Cette action est irrversible.', [{\n              text: 'Annuler',\n              style: 'cancel',\n              onPress: () => resolve(false)\n            }, {\n              text: 'Supprimer tout',\n              style: 'destructive',\n              onPress: () => resolve(true)\n            }]);\n          }\n        });\n      };\n      const confirmed = await confirmDelete();\n      if (!confirmed) return;\n      try {\n        const headers = await getAuthHeaders();\n        await axios.default.delete(`${API_URL}/api/contacts/${contactId}/history`, {\n          headers\n        });\n        await loadData();\n        Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(' Historique supprim!') : Alert.default.alert('', 'Historique supprim!');\n      } catch (err) {\n        console.error('Error deleting history:', err);\n      }\n    };\n    const deleteBetterOffer = async submissionId => {\n      try {\n        const headers = await getAuthHeaders();\n        await axios.default.delete(`${API_URL}/api/better-offers/${submissionId}`, {\n          headers\n        });\n        await loadData();\n      } catch (err) {\n        console.error('Error deleting offer:', err);\n      }\n    };\n    const openClientDetails = client => {\n      setSelectedClient(client);\n      setShowClientModal(true);\n    };\n    const openFollowUpModal = submission => {\n      setSelectedSubmission(submission);\n      const tomorrow = new Date();\n      tomorrow.setDate(tomorrow.getDate() + 1);\n      setFollowUpDate(tomorrow.toISOString().split('T')[0]);\n      setFollowUpNotes(submission.notes || '');\n      setShowFollowUpModal(true);\n    };\n    const saveFollowUp = async () => {\n      if (!selectedSubmission || !followUpDate) return;\n      setSavingFollowUp(true);\n      try {\n        const headers = await getAuthHeaders();\n        await axios.default.put(`${API_URL}/api/submissions/${selectedSubmission.id}/reminder`, {\n          reminder_date: new Date(followUpDate).toISOString(),\n          notes: followUpNotes\n        }, {\n          headers\n        });\n        await loadData();\n        setShowFollowUpModal(false);\n        Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(' Suivi planifi!') : Alert.default.alert('', 'Suivi planifi!');\n      } catch (err) {\n        Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(' Erreur') : Alert.default.alert('Erreur');\n      } finally {\n        setSavingFollowUp(false);\n      }\n    };\n    const newQuoteForClient = client => {\n      setShowClientModal(false);\n      router.push({\n        pathname: '/(tabs)',\n        params: {\n          clientName: client.name,\n          clientEmail: client.email,\n          clientPhone: client.phone\n        }\n      });\n    };\n\n    // Check for better offers (compare new programs with past submissions)\n    const checkForBetterOffers = async () => {\n      setCheckingOffers(true);\n      try {\n        const headers = await getAuthHeaders();\n        const response = await axios.default.post(`${API_URL}/api/compare-programs`, {}, {\n          headers\n        });\n        const {\n          better_offers,\n          count\n        } = response.data;\n        setBetterOffers(better_offers || []);\n        if (count > 0) {\n          Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(` ${count} ${crm.offersFound}`) : Alert.default.alert('', `${count} ${crm.offersFound}`);\n        } else {\n          Platform.default.OS === 'web' ? alert(crm.noNewOffers) : Alert.default.alert('Info', crm.noNewOffers);\n        }\n      } catch (err) {\n        console.error('Error checking offers:', err);\n      } finally {\n        setCheckingOffers(false);\n      }\n    };\n\n    // Approve and send better offer email to client\n    const approveOffer = async submissionId => {\n      setApprovingOffer(submissionId);\n      try {\n        const headers = await getAuthHeaders();\n        await axios.default.post(`${API_URL}/api/better-offers/${submissionId}/approve`, {}, {\n          headers\n        });\n\n        // Reload offers\n        const offersResponse = await
